{
  "texts": [
    "This static analysis provides a high level of confidence as it considers all possible execution paths, unlike measurement-based methods which may not cover all paths exhaustively.",
    "Liang et al. [53] extend this by considering the effects of caches, introducing probabilistic cache states to capture different cache contents at each program point, assuming provided probabilities for conditional branches and loop bounds.SPTA based on probabilities from faults models the occurrence and impact of faults (transient and permanent) on execution times.",
    "By predicting how often these faults cause additional delays (e.g., cache misses due to faulty cache lines), the method estimates the probabilistic timing penalties introduced by these faults, thereby contributing to the WCET estimation.",
    "Hofig et al. [54] develop Failure-Dependent Timing Analysis, combining static WCET analysis with probabilities from a safety analysis model to derive WCET bounds associated with specific fault situations, assuming independence of sensor failures.",
    "Hardy et al. [55] present a method to statically determine pWCET bounds for architectures with faulty instruction caches."
  ]
}